          {
            "id": 355285751950157,
            "definition": {
              "type": "note",
              "content": "### **OSPF Interface States:**\n\nThe **STATE** metric is the current OSPF interface state.\n\n**(1) down, (2) loopback, (3) waiting, (4) point to point, (5) designated router, (6) backup designated router, (7) other designated router**\n\n---------------------\n\nThe **RETRANS** metric is the number of seconds between link state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface.",
              "background_color": "gray",
              "font_size": "14",
              "text_align": "left",
              "show_tick": false,
              "tick_pos": "50%",
              "tick_edge": "right"
            },
            "layout": {
              "x": 0,
              "y": 4,
              "width": 6,
              "height": 3
            }
          },
          {
            "id": 5817781938376,
            "definition": {
              "type": "note",
              "content": "### **OSPF Neighbor States:**\n\nThe **STATE** metric is the state of the relationship with this neighbor.\n\n**(1) down, (2) attempt, (3) init, (4) two way, (5) exchange start, (6) exchange, (7) loading, (8) full** \n\n---------------------\n\nThe **EVENTS** metric is the number of times this neighbor relationship has changed state or an error has occurred. ",
              "background_color": "gray",
              "font_size": "14",
              "text_align": "left",
              "show_tick": false,
              "tick_pos": "50%",
              "tick_edge": "right"
            },
            "layout": {
              "x": 6,
              "y": 4,
              "width": 6,
              "height": 3
            }
          },
